(7, 'R007', '', '', 'Located in a freestanding 34X80 foot building, Bob''s free-lanced transition era layout is contains a mountain scene with spectacular bridges, a city scene and a port complete with cargo ship. Bob''s 2,694 feet (over 80,000 ties) of hand-laid track includes a seven track passenger station, industrial switching district and a large classification yard. Equipment inventory in Bob''s O scale empire includes 117 locomotives, 43 cabeese and over 1,000 freight cars.																	', 'O', '', '', '100%', '34 x 80', '', '', '', 'yes', 2, 'N', 'N', '', 'Bob', 'Jakl', '(209) 743-7812', '', '', '5034 Mykleoaks Road', 'Mariposa', 'CA', '', '', NULL),
(8, 'R008', '', '', 'Dave''s 2,000 feet of hand-laid track occupies a 30 X 70 foot area on the second floor of a freestanding building. The design is a loose interpretation of the SP from Sacramento to Sparks, but Santa Fe and Sierra Railroad steam locomotives roam the rails as well. xxx feet of snowsheds protect Dave''s mainline from that precipitation, which has covered the southern half of this spectacularly sceniced layout. Downgrade from the snow is a large engine facility with turntable and roundhouse.', 'O', '', '', '100%', '30 x 70', '', '', '', 'yes', 5, 'N', 'N', '', 'Dave', 'Viale', '(209) 742-5737', '', '', '5652 Pilot Peak Road', 'Mariposa', 'CA', '', '', NULL),
(9, 'R009', '', '', 'Tom''s Lionel trains are certainly not a &quot;Lionel layout&quot;. This freelanced transition era layout is fully sceniced and ballasted with many scratch-built structures and is definitely not a toy train set-up. Tom''s 24 X 36 foot layout features a liftable bridge for access into the central viewing area.', 'O', '', '', '100%', '24 x 36', '', '', '', 'Analog', 6, 'N', 'N', '', 'Tom', 'Davis', '(209) 742-6131', '', '', '4838 Usona Road', 'Mariposa', 'CA', '', '', NULL),
(11, 'R011', 'Glenwood & Black Creek NG (and Central California Coast SG)', '', 'The G&amp;BC narrow gauge represents 1/2 of a mountain division. Heavy freight and passenger trains work from and to several staging yards across the 2 1/2% grades over Cumbres pass - most require helpers. In between 8 towns and industries are serviced by peddler freights. There is also a 35 scale mile heavy branch line regularly in use, and a branch and facilities depicting the West Side Lumber Company. The standard gauge loops through the layout and emulates the Southern Pacific. The layout is 98% sceniced.', 'HO HOn', 'Free lanced', '1930''s to 1960''s Cal', '', '14 X 33 plus side room', '242''', 'Point to Point (but connected lo', 'Self devised card system', 'DCC and sound', 1, '', '', '', 'Jim', 'Vail', '831-423-7962', 'Afternoon (12:01pm -- 5:59pm)', 'akacoot@comcast.net', '760 Graham Hill Road', 'Santa Cruz', 'CA', '95060-1437', '', NULL),
(12, 'R012', 'Mystic Mountain Railroad', '', 'A back country shortline loosely set in the early 1900''s consisting of 1200'' of code 250 Nickel Silver track. The railroad can be run as a single large loop or two smaller loops, with several passing sidings, two small yards, six spurs, a wye and a reversing loop for turning trains, and many tunnels and bridges. The Mountain Division runs over rugged mountains and deep canyons, necessitating many steel bridges, tunnels, and a large, complex helix. A scratch built turntable/roundhouse is located at the North End yard in the Mountain Division. Trains can also be run point-to-point between the two yards. Trains are track and battery-powered, radio controlled using Train Engineer, and Revolution with SoundTraxx sound systems. Realistic train operations can be run for added interest. One unique feature is the use of concrete rock wall castings painted with artist acrylics. A panoramic view of Silicon Valley serves as a natural backdrop to the railroad. New are a custom mine/ore processing p', 'G', '', '', NULL, '', '', 'Garden, dual-oval', '', 'Radio', NULL, 'u', 'u', 'http://www.mysticmountainarts.com/MMRR/', 'Ray', 'Turner', '408-272-9234', 'Evening (6:01pm -- 9:59pm)', 'ray@mysticmountainarts.com', '10251 Kenny Ln', 'San Jose', 'CA', '95127', '', NULL),
(14, 'R014', 'Silicon Valley Lines', '', 'Founded in 1979, Silicon Valley Lines (SVL) is a freelance HO Scale Model Railroad Club located in San Jose, California. Construction of the current layout began in late 2000 and is located in the basement of an industrial building near downtown San Jose. The railroad occupies a 23'' x 72'' space, and is a multi-level design built using commercial steel C-channel as a benchwork system with over 600 feet of mainline. The upper level is a single-track division, while much of the lower level is double tracked. The layout features two large operating yards, as a well as ample hidden, yet accessible staging.\n\nWe operate using NCE DCC, and utilize Direct Traffic Control (DTC) operating rules.', 'HO', 'freelance', 'freelance', NULL, '72''x23''', '>600 feet', 'Multi-deck around the walls', 'DTC', 'DCC', NULL, 'y', 'n', 'http://www.siliconvalleylines.com', 'Eric', 'Eggel', '408-203-6910', 'Afternoon (12:01pm -- 5:59pm)', 'svl@siliconvalleylines.com', '148 E. Virginia Street', 'San Jose', 'CA', '95112', '', NULL),
(15, 'R015', 'South Bay Historical Railroad Society', '', 'SBHRS operates two model train displays, HO and N-scale layouts in the historic Santa Clara Depot (Opened in 1864). Both layouts include extensive signalling. Like many model railroads, they are works in progress and are undergoing constant change. Both layouts have many handcrafted scenes, such as a winery, dam, two helixes, row homes and a yacht harbor (N-scale) and meat packing, lumber mill, oil storage tanks, plus a replica of the San Jose Southern Pacific Depot, ca 1950 (HO-scale).\r\n\r\nScenery is about 90% complete on both layouts.', 'HO & N', 'Emphasis on SP, UP, ', 'Thru 1959; western s', '', 'HO: 15 x 80 ft. N: 1', 'HO: 200 ft. N: Up to', '', 'HO: two mainlines and point-to-p', 'HO: DCC. N: DCC and ', 5, '', '', 'http://www.sbhrs.org', 'Joe', 'Hoffmann', '408-296-7779', 'Morning (9:01am -- 11:59am)', 'johoff@ix.netcom.com', 'Santa Clara Caltrain Depot 1005 Railroad Avenue', 'Santa Clara', 'CA', '95050', '', NULL),
(16, 'R016', 'Tuolumne Forks', '', 'Scenery is complete and detailed. The railroad is a logging and tourist line with sawmills and a large hotel set in the Roaring Twenties. I also have an On30 limestone layout with kilns, a stave mill, and cooperage, above my workbench. There is also a collection of pioneer On3 models.', 'O On3 On30', 'freelance', 'Sierras in the Roari', '', '25 x34', '?', 'bent in loop', 'run trains around', 'CVP Easy DCC', 1, '', '', '', 'Bob', 'Brown', '650-948-9361', 'Morning (9:01am -- 11:59am)', 'gazette@att.net', 'Street address 985 Campbell Ave.', 'Los Altos', 'CA', '94024', '', NULL),
(17, 'R017', 'Cumberland West', '', 'Two railroads run side by side in western Maryland and northern West Virginia. Both railroads have major junctions in Cumberland and interchange traffic at several points. The B&amp;O has Color Position Light signals controled by five towers with touch-screen CTC panels. 30% Sceniced.', 'HO', 'B&O and Western Mary', 'Cumberland, MD 1953', '', '1200 Sq Ft', '180 ft each RR', 'One leval panorama - Single stag', 'B&O - double track towers Rule 2', 'Digitrax DCC, Tower ', 1, '', '', '', 'David', 'Parks', '650-961-7644', 'Morning (9:01am -- 11:59am)', 'bearwestern@comcast.net', '1281 Windimer Drive', 'Los Altos', 'CA', '94024-7116', '', NULL),
(18, 'R018', 'New York Central -- Valley Division', '', 'This large S scale layout represents the NYC in the Catskill Mountains in 1948.  Steam is resisting diesel pressure to retire early, but is losing the battle.  Hauling long freights and fast passenger trains over the mountainous terrain is a routine daily task on this layout.  Scenery is 95% complete with a detailed backdrop, huge mountains, tall waterfall, long bridges and an unusual lightning/thunderstorm animation.  Industrial areas include a coal mine, logging camp, sawmill, oil refinery and a city area.   Not only has Ed been featured in Great Model Railroads in 2005,  Model Railroader in November 2008,  Model Railroad Hobbyist Magazine in October of 2009 and NMRA Magazine in September 2010 his layout was part of PBS TV''s program TRACKS AHEAD. ', 'S Sn3', 'NYC and WSLCo.', '1948 in the Catskill', '', '20'' x 30''', '305''', 'Very Interesting', 'Yes....!!', 'DCC', 1, '', '', '', 'Edward', 'Loizeaux', '650-962-1577 *no', 'Morning (9:01am -- 11:59am)', 'Loizeaux@SBCGlobal.net', '2221 Via Maderos', 'Los Altos', 'CA', '94024-7113', '', NULL),
(19, 'R019', 'Sonora Pacific & Southern Pacific', '', 'HO/HOn3 layout depicting a California narrow gauge railroad interchanging with the Southern Pacific in the 1940''s thru 50''s. It is a series of scenes, each with its own theme, set apart effectively by scenic dividers. It features very fine rock work &amp; fantastic scenery. There are freelanced depictions of Los Angeles, Westside Lumber, &amp; a gold mine/mill complex.  Featured in Railroad Model Craftsman and in Narrow Gauge &amp; Short Line Gazette.', 'HO / HOn3', 'SP & Several Califor', '1940''s & 50''s Califo', '', '20''  X  20''', '80 ft.', 'Bent dog bone N.G.,  & bent figu', '', 'DC Radio Controlled', 1, '', '', 'http://fjohnlabarba.com/25401.html', 'F. John', 'LaBarba', '831-423-1109', 'Evening (6:01pm -- 9:59pm)', 'fjohnlab@earthlink.net', '741 Redwood Drive', 'Santa Cruz', 'CA', '95060', '', NULL),
(20, 'R020', 'D&RGW Durlin Branch', '', 'The Durlin Branch is a free-lance mountain branch line of the narrow gauge D&amp;RGW fourth division hauling general freight, coal, ore concentrates, livestock and passengers. The branch ties into the San Juan Extension mainline in Chama NM, with both Durango CO to the west and Alamosa CO to the east represented by staging. The Durlin branch line takes off from Chama and climbs a steady 3.8% grade through Cresco and Toltec Tunnel up to Carrumba where the line splits. One line continues on to Fritz Park, then descends a 4% grade through Resin Creek to Durlin. The other branch serves a large coal mine at Flint. Steam locomotives rule on the narrow gauge, serviced by an animated ashpit, water tanks and coal tower. The pace is relaxed as befits a low density traffic pattern with saw-bys, double headers and doubling the hill all in adays work. Scenery is 90+ % complete.', '1/4" = 1 ft ', 'D&RGW narrow gauge', '< 1936;Southwest Col', '', '17ft X 27ft', '120 ft', 'Point to Point, Double Deck, Wal', 'TT&TO, 4:1 fast clocks, CC&WB wi', 'DCC (Easy DCC, radio', 1, '', '', '', 'Dave', 'Adams', '408-244-1850', 'Evening (6:01pm -- 9:59pm)', 'dadamsc16@sbcglobal.net', '1464 Lamore Drive', 'San Jose', 'CA', '95130', '', 1),
(21, 'R021', 'D&ELP', '', 'The region is the area between Deming and El Paso, with Deming and El Paso represented. Interchanges with the BNSF are modeled in Deming and in El Paso. The SP crossing of the Rio Grande west of El Paso is depicted. The era is modern. Scenery is about 20% complete, perhaps a little more.', 'HO', 'SP', 'Modern, southern New', NULL, 'L shaped triple deck', '240 feet', 'Out and back, continuous loop, d', 'Car Card', 'DCC', NULL, 'n', 'y', '', 'Mark', 'Stearns', '831-899-3837', 'Evening (6:01pm -- 9:59pm)', 'steaks@juno.com', '1331 Waring Street', 'Seaside', 'CA', '93955', '', NULL),
(22, 'R022', 'Union Pacific in Niles Canyon', '', 'The layout is set in the East Bay Area in 1999. The railroad represents the former Western Pacific San Jose and 1st Subdivisions, now the UP Niles, Oakland and Milpitas Subdivisions. The railroad is a branchline which supports an Auto plant (NUMMI) and a number of smaller industries.\n\nDispatching is by TCS (using CATS) which replicates a Digicon console. All signals are repeated on color lite signals above the layout. A unique feature of the layout is that there is no yardmaster, only a clerk. This is because the prototype Milpitas Yard has no permanent switcher. The clerk is responsible for managing the yard and the neighboring NUMMI complex, writing switch lists to instruct the crews where to place cars. All crews do their own work when passing through the yard. We expect the layout to be 70% sceniced by AS X2011W', 'HO', 'Union Pacific', 'Spring 1999, East Ba', NULL, '12'' x 35''', '120 foot visible', 'Folded dogbone with staging', 'dispaching is CTC, car forwardin', 'NCE DCC Radio', NULL, 'n', 'n', 'http://www.bayrails.com/layouts2.php?m=neumann', 'Seth', 'Neumann', '650-965-4687', 'Afternoon (12:01pm -- 5:59pm)', 'sneumann@pacbell.net', '2712 Katrina Way', 'Moutain View', 'CA', '94040', '', NULL),
(23, 'R023', 'ATSF Coast Lines, Fourth District, Valley Division', '', 'HO Scale proto-freelanced extension of the Santa Fe in the early 1970s from the San Francisco Bay Area to Portland; modeled portion runs from the Central Valley town of Chico to McCloud just south of Mt. Shasta in a purpose-built 30'' x 49''room. Double deck point to point, mainline 85% complete with aprox. 550 feet of track in place, permanent track is all hand laid. 30% scenicked. Dispatcher; interlocking tower; large yard with two switch crews and yardmaster/hostler; small yard with a full time switcher; heavy duty freight with some passenger; local switching; branchline. Wireless NCE DCC; FRS radios; Track Warrants; car cards and waybills. 46"duck under to enter layout during session.', 'HO', 'Santa Fe', 'Early 1970s, between', NULL, '1240 sq ft, 30ft x 4', 'Approx 550ft', 'Double deck point-to-point walka', 'Track Warrants, Car Cards/Waybil', 'Wireless NCE DCC', NULL, 'n', 'y', '', 'Rick', 'Fortin', '408-266-7245', 'Morning (9:01am -- 11:59am)', 'rick-r@pacbell.net', '5305 Alan Ave', 'San Jose', 'CA', '95124', '', NULL),
(24, 'R024', 'ATSF&SP', '', 'Diesel to steam transition, heavy on steam. Emphasis on extreme detailing and smooth running. About 50% sceniced with generic Ca theme. Double track mainline, 6 track passenger station, 13 track yard, and 14 stall roundhouse with 18 garden track. Tsunami sound.', 'O Scale', 'Santa Fe and Souther', '1947-1951, genric Ca', NULL, '20'' X 40''', '110''', 'Double track loop with large yar', 'Basically just watching highly d', 'DCC', NULL, 'n', 'y', '', 'Gary', 'Schrader', '408-227-9491', 'Afternoon (12:01pm -- 5:59pm)', 'gs-sj@earthlink.net', '4201 Kingspark Drive', 'San Jose', 'CA', '95136', '', NULL),
