(162, 'R162', 'Steve''s Western Pacific Railroad', '', 'Layout covers from San Francisco to Salt Lake City with Reno and Tidewater branches. Fully signal with CTC.  Computer generated waybill system. 1970 era. 4 large yards. 9 passing sidings. All diesel power. Includes prototypically correct scratch built models of the Oakland and Salt Lake depots (Salt Lake was featured  in MR trackside photo section).', 'HO', '', '', '50%', '30 X 56', '', '', '', 'Chubb w/ infared throttles', 2, 'N', 'N', 'http://members.bigvalley.net/norma', 'Steve', 'Hayes', '(209) 536-1847', '', '', '16241 Fleetwood Street', 'Sonora', 'CA', '', '', 1),
