(61, 'P408', 'FOLSOM HISTORICAL SITES', '2011-07-06 00:00:00', '2011-07-06 00:00:00', 'When the Folsom Powerhouse opened in 1895 it was the first power system to transmit high voltage alternating electric current over long distance power lines by sending power to Sacramento, twenty-two miles away.  That feat has earned it a spot in the National Register of Historic Places.   Our docent led tour of the Powerhouse is one of three stops we will make after arriving in Folsom. Our other stops are the Folsom Railroad Museum operated by the El Dorado Historical Society Railroad and the Folsom History Museum. \r\n<p/>\r\nThis tour will travel via Sacramento Regional Transit''s Light Rail System from the Convetnion Center to end of the blue line in Downtown Folsom.  All of our stops in Folsom are within walking distance of the light rail stop.\r\n', 1, '', 0.00, 0, '0', 0, 0),
